Runtime relationships
---------------------

- Hearthstone and Hearthstone Battlegrounds are products of Blizzard
  Entertainment. Their names, marks, game text, and assets remain the
  property of their respective owners.
- Hearthstone Deck Tracker is the runtime host. Bob Coach does not distribute
  HDT binaries. Any public plugin distribution requires a separate
  compatibility and permission review.
- HearthDb is supplied by the user's HDT installation and is licensed by
  HearthSim under the MIT License. Bob Coach does not bundle HearthDb.dll.
- Newtonsoft.Json and other HDT-provided assemblies are runtime dependencies
  supplied by the user's HDT installation and are not bundled by Bob Coach.
- Firestone/Zero to Heroes is named only as historical evaluation context.
  The current public build does not request, cache, display, bundle, or
  redistribute its trinket statistics. Historical user caches are not read,
  migrated, or deleted. See DATA_SOURCES.md.
- The initial public build does not display or prioritize trinket-offer choice
  prompts. Its
  equipped-trinket effects are original Bob Coach logic driven by HDT match
  state and versioned local CardId rules, without Firestone statistics. The
  `hdt-1.53.5-hearthdb-2026-07-22-r3` ruleset covers 16 exact CardIds audited
  against a maintainer-provided HearthDb snapshot; this includes the local
  `BG30_MagicItem_705` Oilcan upgrade-cost rule. The snapshot is not copied
  into the repository or release package, and tests use synthetic state only.
- HearthstoneJSON/hsdata and Gamerhub data remain subject to their own rights
  and terms. The production plugin currently does not drive an external
  trinket-statistics request path.
- Bob Coach does not currently integrate with, fetch, scrape, bundle, or
  redistribute HSReplay data. Any future integration requires a separate
  review of the applicable terms and permissions.

Release restriction
-------------------

The formal plugin DLL contains no JSON data resources. Historical datasets,
raw third-party responses, development reports, logs, replays, profiles, and
user-local HearthDb content are excluded from the offline package.

The source repository is public. v0.2.0-beta.1 is the historical public beta,
  and v0.2.0-beta.2 is the current release line. The beta.1 preview builder is
  retired and cannot recreate a historical package from beta.2 inputs. Every GitHub Release, upload,
or public distribution still requires separate explicit owner authorization
after the applicable validation and third-party review are complete.

All product names and trademarks are used only to identify compatibility,
data provenance, or non-use boundaries. No trademark license or endorsement
is implied.
